I think this SCP is trying to do too little with too many words. I read the testing logs, and I absolutely loved them. I think all you need for this particular SCP is a short few paragraphs describing the tapes and nothing else  bit of it. There's a metric fuckton of SCPs that already do that. Furthermore, I don't think the box adds anything to the article.

So, my suggestion: cut the article so that it's 1/3rd of its current length, have it be about the tapes and nothing else, and leave the testing logs as they are now (because right now, the logs are absolutely the best part of this SCP). As it is, the article itself is not enough  for me to upvote, but the concept is interesting enough that a downvote feels dickish. So, no vote.

EDIT: In cutting, I'd also include the addendums and the good doctor's note in italics. The note can be summarized with a few words inside the body of the description  as a note, the tone feels very off, with a doctor losing his shit like that. The addendums effectively add nothing to the article, and should instead be carried over into the testing logs, if you feel them necessary.





